The food used to be great and cheap, however, the prices went up and buffet quality went down. Not to mention the main cook has a attitude issue.  I didn’t mind the price slightly going up as it was still the cheapest in the area, but now they are replacing products with cheaper alternative and worse taste.  They recently tried eggs with spinach and feta cheese, it was great but they stopped making it.  The sausage links used to be great, but recently I noticed the taste is off.  The main buffer cook is very nasty to the customers. Few months ago I remember someone asked him if there is any more eggs with vegetables coming and he gave a nasty response. Recently I asked him if any more sausage links are coming because I seen something frying in the oil, he told me “no more” but I decided to wait and seen they taking them out from the oil. I questioned him why he was lying and he just acted stupid.  The cashier and other staff behind the counter are great, that’s the only reason I’m giving it 3 instead of just 1 star.

I ordered a panini. Not only did it take them 20 minutes to warm up when I took my first bite the panini was ice cold. The bread was hot but the meat and cheese inside was still frozen. They don’t seem to care about the quality of their food and it shows.

This place used to have one of the best buffet for breakfast but now they are to skimpy with the selection and started to charge for the coffee if you have less than $3.00 per item. Had $5.70 worth and they tried to charge for the extra coffee. Poor selection of product in the morning and prices have gone up significantly. Will not be going back I guess McDonalds breakfast it will be. So sad used to go here at least 3x a week months ago. Now I remember why I stopped.

I never had a problem coming to this establishment until today. Usually come in for breakfast or lunch buffet and I always pay with my card.  Today the women at the register said I can not use my card because it is less than $5.00.  I asked her "Where is the sign located so that patrons would know there was a the $5.00 minimum is needed to use ta credit or debit card?"  The women just looked at me and stated I need to purchase more items to charge my card.  She just kept saying it was a $5.00 dollar minimum.  I understand some establishments require a minimum to charge on credit but they make sure customers are aware of their policy.  What irritated me the most is that she kept insisting that I purchase more than what I had. Which made no sense... this was the worst case of Poor Customer Service!!!!!!

Love it .  great prices . excellent customer service.

I wish I could give this place less than one star. I used to frequent this place daily for breakfast, but stopped. Every time I would come in to get breakfast and attempt to make my order they would blatantly look passed me and service Spanish speakers who came in behind me. I thought it might have been a mistake, but it happened more than once and when I tried to address it they brushed me off and took the next person every time. My coworker thought I was exaggerating until he saw it for himself.

Usually come in for breakfast buffet and I always pay with my card.  Today, I did not buy coffee or a drink and the women at the register said I can not use my card because it is less than $5.00.  I informed her the establishment does not have a sign anywhere stating that a $5.00 minimum is needed to use the card.  The women just looked at me and stated I need to purchase two items to charge on my card.  I asked for management and  she refused to call management.  I understand some establishments require a minimum to charge on credit but they make sure customers are aware of their policy.  Poor customer service especially to someone that  comes in everyday.

Great food

We use Dante's regularly for events at the office. The staff is very professional, friendly and accommodating. Food is of an amazing quality. We usually do breakfast spreads. The bagels are extraordinary and the wide variety  of pastries offered leave all in attendance satisfied.  Definitely recommend this establishment.

Went here last night for a quick meal after work and received the worst customer service ever. I ordered a cheeseburger deluxe that was undercooked, I took two bites and returned it and asked for a well cooked burger, which I was promised a new burger afteewards. The alleged manager took my container downstairs and returned with the same tray a few minutes later. She had sat my entire burger back on the grill (the burger I had bitten off of) after telling me I would receive a new one. After I asked for my money back and she told me I couldn't get my money back, that it was now hers, she only gave me 3 dollars for an 8 dollars meal which I did not eat and told me my service was not needed after I was very cordial with her. Not to mention they were spraying windex over the open food bar. Very unsanitary and rude customer service!
I have been waiting for delivery for 1 hour and 20 minutes now. I ordered an individual pizza. ONE.

Very good breakfast. Prices are reasonable especially for downtown Manhattan  Update Fall 2013: Food has become inconsistent. I've gotten stale rolls and bacon that has tasted funny, maybe it was old. Some days they are great, sometimes they are not. I'd rather pay more and get the same thing every time.
